<table width="auto"  border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td colspan=3>House Bill/Resolution NO. <b>HB05190</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>FULL TITLE : AN ACT PROMOTING THE USE OF URBAN FARMING IN THE COUNTRY'S METROPOLITAN AREAS TO ADDRESS FOOD SECURITY CONCERNS AND REGENERATE ECOSYSTEM FUNCTIONS, APPROPRIATING FUNDS THEREFOR, AND FOR ANY OTHER PURPOSE</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SHORT TITLE : “ The Urban Agriculture Act Of 2017 ”</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>ABSTRACT : 
Defines the terms “Urban Agriculture” and “Vertical Farming”; Involves the application of intensive production methods such as the using and reusing of urban sources and wastes; Also involves animal husbandry aquaculture, agro-forestry and horticulture; Employs the concepts of indoor agriculture in skyscrapers and other modern buildings; Integrates these methods in the academic curriculum of Institutions studying courses on Agriculture; Practical Arts, Home Economics, etc., and also incorporates its concept in the NSTP or the CMT.
</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>PRINCIPAL AUTHOR/S : <b>ALEJANO, GARY C.</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>DATE FILED : 2017-03-02</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SIGNIFICANCE: NATIONAL</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>CO-AUTHORS (Journal Entries) :</td></tr><tr><td>1. Sy-Alvarado (086 2017-05-08)</td><td>2. Tambunting (095 2017-05-29)</td><tr><td>3. Violago (000 2018-02-19)</td><tr><td colspan=3><b>ACTIONS TAKEN BY THE COMMITTEE</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>COMMITEE HEARINGS/ACTIONS:</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3><b>&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp1. Measure approved by the Committee on 2017-10-10</b><tr><td colspan=3>&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp-Approved the substitute bill with HBs 2818, 4337, 4354, 4422 and 4805</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3><b>&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp2. Committee Report approved on 2019-02-11</b><tr><td colspan=3>MOTHER BILL:&nbspHB09105</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3><b>ACTIONS TAKEN BY THE COMMITTEE ON RULES</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>REFERRAL TO THE COMMITTEE ON FOOD SECURITY ON 2017-03-07</td></tr></table>